			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Even tho the first header reminded me of communist era propaganda I do agree with a lot of what is said..
<br />

<br />
Yes, I am an uber mage and in the past (and I still stand by everything Ive said) I've made note that content does indeed need to scale upwards to keep people playing..
<br />

<br />
However as before raiding becomes hollow and you forget what really made EQ fun.  That is the grouping experience and sense of accomplishment in small numbers.  While yes some fights in raids *are* difficult its generally only a forumla of Tank Durability and healing the raid, if you aren't a cleric or a tank you're generally a nameless face that is replacable by any other nameless face leading to the fact that loot is the only reason to raid.  For me, and Im sure others it's not that interesting to only get loot.
<br />

<br />
Not to mention the problems with the loot itself being subpar or poorly planned leads to frustration and loss of morale.  If you're going to cater to the high end guilds do it right please.   The mobs and encounters I've seen in Gates *are* really good no doubt about it (Once fixed) however the loot has been dissapointing, and more frustrating for casters as our loot seems very fragmented and unfocused.
<br />

<br />
Like I said in the past I agree that the game should recieve content upwards not down, however I do *not* agree on shutting out the casual gamers.  There *has* to be good content for them, as even I like to play in that style it's what I enjoy but I want to get the best items so im forced to raid.
<br />

<br />
In other words, create raid content but dont sacrifice the game's soul for it.  If there needs to be less raids, or gasp longer development time to create a real expansion again then so be it.  1 expansion a y ear is what we expected in the past, now it's 2 every year which is very noticable on how small they are<br />_________________<br /><br>
<br />
<img border=0 src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg" />
<br />
<br>
<br />
