			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Wow that was quite a read. I am not sure where to begin but I want a piece of this so:
<br />

<br />

<br />
 1) <span style="font-weight: bold">Uberguilds</span>- Yes, Ubers eat content like a fat lady at a buffet...but that is what the content is there for yes? A part of this sounds alot like "uber envy". I am not in an uber guild (or a raiding guild for that matter) but if I wanted to join one to see this content I would. I choose to be the "casual player" out of choice <span style="font-style: italic">and</span> necessity as I am a husband / father / worker bee.
<br />

<br />
 2) <span style="font-weight: bold">The "fun factor" is gone</span>- "Fun" is relative ; what may be <span style="font-style: italic">fun</span> for you may be a <span style="font-style: italic">headache</span> for me  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" /> . I have a simple solution: I keep a couple FPS games handy ( atm they are Call of Duty and Halo) that I log off Everquest and play when I can't find a group etc etc. The day I started Everquest and stumbled out of Qeynos gate to kill my first rat was magic. After 4 years I am a bit jaded but the "fun" is still there for me.
<br />

<br />
 3) <span style="font-weight: bold">GM services outsourced</span>- to INDIA?? Hell I thought only Dell did this! Wow I can't wait till I petition and talk to "Carl"!  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
 4) <span style="font-weight: bold">The Fabled stuff that was going on was a step in the right direction</span>.- Huh?? Over a period of 3 weeks I checked 6 different "camps" and was told the <span style="font-style: italic">average</span> wait was 9 hours. You can have that crap ( see the end of # 1 above).
<br />

<br />
 5) <span style="font-weight: bold">SOE</span>- is a business. They are not in it to provide jobs. Or a service. They are there to make money. If the service they provide ( game content) makes a load of cash they will keep the status quo. If their product does not sell ( low sell rate of GoD compared to other expansions) then they will take notice. I did not buy GoD and have no intention of doing so. I also will not buy "OoW". It's rather pointless from the chair I am sitting in as I have yet to bite into most content from PoP ( or SoL for that matter). Hit 'em where it hurts...the accounting room...and they will stand and deliver.
<br />

<br />
 6) <span style="font-weight: bold">The Old World zone needs a makeover</span>- Bad. I ran thru Freeport the other day and was hit with a wave of nostalgia. I remember when the NFP bank was.....oh nevermind <sniffles> <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="Crying or Very sad" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
 7) <span style="font-weight: bold">Every server needs it's own GM</span>- I used to play D&amp;D years ago ( 20 acually) and the DM controlled storytelling and pace. Every server needs it's own special GM; not to answer petitions but to evolve a story. I suggest hiring struggling Fantasy writers to script events etc. I could work. Really. <img src="images/smiles/icon_idea.gif" alt="Idea" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />

<br />
 Well that's about all. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
   Mud</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
