			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, so here is my take on this-
<br />

<br />
They release PoP.  PoP is for the big raid guilds.  They all have something to do.  Most of us can't see more than 8-10 zones in PoP unless we join the raid guild.  (Later, they open up zones by levels).
<br />

<br />
They release GoD.  Now GoD is designed for the people who have SUBSTANTIALLY completed PoP in order to progress SUBSTANTIALLY into GoD zones.  At least Elemental, if not Time/Quarm kills.
<br />

<br />
Then they announce OoW, and it's going to be for people who have completed much of GoD. . . 
<br />

<br />
Making expansions that continue to only give the big raid guilds content is eventually going to give you a smaller and smaller amount of people interested in the expansions.
<br />

<br />
I'm a casual player.  I'm still raiding PoP on occasion.  I'm not Sol Ro flagged yet.  I still need MM, Agnarr, Saryn, RZ.  I have 1 piece of "uber raid" gear.  I'm not ready for an expansion the requires me to be Time flagged.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">So what happend to quests anyway?</span>
<br />

<br />
Remember the "newspapers"?  They would tell us of upcoming events/changes?  Things that gave us clues about new content being added and quests to perform?
<br />

<br />
I used to park mules by the newspaper vendors and check them every patch day!  I couldn't wait to see if a new quest was put in.  I finished the Qeynos 4th Badge quest the day it went live!  I couldn't wait to log in and see if something like that was added.  That whole story line with the plague and zones changing to match was very exciting to me.
<br />

<br />
How many people did the anniversary quest for the fireworks stick?  I'm betting MANY <span style="text-decoration: underline">THOUSANDS</span> of players.  Why?  It's a worthless item with no stats and all it does is make fireworks??  But it was something NEW that EVERYONE could do and enjoy.  It wasn't some new zone with trash mobs that hit for 1200s that requires an Elemental geared Tank and 2 healers to survive. . .
<br />

<br />
LDoN worked for us.  It was content that every level could do.  But it was a bit lackluster as far as story-lines go.  Go here, kill stuff, report back, over and over and over.  Certainly not the depth of what we saw in Velious.
<br />

<br />
But the fact is you don't really need new zones for the 1-60 level people.  There are plenty of them out there.  What you need is more excitement, more quests, more reasons to go see those zones that are already there.  That firework stick quests made me go see several places I hadn't visted in years.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure what Epic 2.0 is going to be like.  But if it envolves major raid only content that I have no chance of doing, I'm going to contine my stance and not buy OoW.<br />_________________<br /><DIV *****"position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=FF0000)"><a *****"font-weight:bold; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796  target="new-window"><b>Master Zacatac Soulwanderer</b></a></div>"1450 Club" Tradeskiller
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>A_necro wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I think it's because we have rune, FD, root, DA, levant, fear, mez, potential slows, and more manaregen/power than most mages. . .  <span style="font-style: italic"><span style="font-weight: bold">Mages are limited once the pet is gone.</span></span></td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
