				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have summarized some of the problem lists put forth in the starting post.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">FIX THE BUGS and STOP IGNORING YOUR CUSTOMERS</span> 
<br />
ONE DAY WE WILL GET ON THE TEST SERVER AND REPORT THE BUGS INSTEAD OF COMPLAINING. ALSO, WE WILL REALIZE THAT OUR WISH IS NOT THEIR COMMAND. THIS IS LIKE MAILING A CELEBRITY -- YOU DONT ALWAYS GET A REPLY.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">POPULATE OLD UNUSED ZONES WITH NEW CONTENT </span>
<br />
THEN WE CAN MOVE ON TO REPOPULATING THE NEW ZONES THAT ARE NOW UNUSED BECAUSE THE OLD ZONES ARE MADE ATTRACTIVE.  EVENTUALLY THERE WILL BE NOTHING NEW IN EVERQUEST JUST THE SAME MOBS WITH DIFFERENT LOOTS AND EXPERIENCE. O JOY.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">STOP PANDERING TO UBERGUILDS and FOCUS ON CONTENT FOR NORMAL PEOPLE </span>
<br />
SOMEHOW I AM SO DUMB I MISSED THE ENTIRE LDON AND YKESHA EXPANSION. HOW IT HAPPENED IS BEYOND ME, BUT THERE YOU GO. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">FIRE MORDEN RASP and CREATE A MORE COMPELLING EPIC STORYLINE</span> 
<br />
Now I actually do agree with this. How many nations and cities of power would let someone like that gather that much influence. Why this band of dumb jocks and fastidious mages can figure out what no one in Erudin or Felwithe or Neriak can is beyond me. And please, get someone experience in writing stories to do the scripts. I am tired of a giant booming voice deafening my ringing ears with a unending scream of gutteral beastial hatred. Less descriptors please.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">HIRE MORE DEVS, QA and GAMEMASTERS </span>
<br />
I AM NOT A BUSINESS MAJOR. BUT HERE I WILL PRETEND TO RUN ONE, AS IT IS A WELL ESTABLISHED FACT THAT MONEY DOES INDEED GROW ON TREES.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">PUT THE QUEST BACK INTO EVERQUEST </span>
<br />
THERE ARE QUESTS OUT THERE THAT WORK AND PRODUCE POWERFUL ITEMS BUT I AM NOT SATISFIED. MAKE FUNS QUESTS. I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT FUN IS. PERHAPS A POWERFUL REWARD FOR VERY LITTLE WORK SO I CAN GET A JOLT OF EXCITEMENT DURING THE TWO HOURS I WORK ON IT.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">MAKE EVERQUEST FUN AGAIN </span>
<br />
IT STOPPED BEING FUN FOR ME. A SELECT GROUP OF PEOPLE WHO BROWSE THIS SITE SEEM TO POST AGREEMENTS WITH ME SO OBVIOUSLY IT IS NOT FUN FOR EVERYONE. BY THE WAY, I HAVE NOT TAKEN STATISTICS AND THE TERM SELECTION BIAS HAS NO APPLICATION HERE. EVEN MORE CURIOUS IS THE FACT THAT I PLAY A GAME THAT IS NOT FUN FOR ENTERTAINMENT BUT LET US GLOSS OVER THAT.
<br />

<br />
Can EverQuest be saved? It seems very unlikely with the kind of people playing it. Just like the 44 car pile ups on the interstate happening every year I seriously doubt that these people can change their style of driving. The morning fog is looming ahead on the interstate and many will simply push the accelerator when the time comes. The real problem is the culture of immaturity and chronic ego inflating at public boards which created this crazed horde we refer to as a mob. At least Smedley has finally realized there is a problem. He must placate a bunch of 2 year olds. 
<br />

<br />
I urge Woody and everyone... yada yada yada.
<br />

<br />
Thank you.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101077/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Hata Takushi</a>
<br />
<span style="color: maroon">"In the beginning, the universe was created. This has made a lot of people angry and is generally thought to have been a bad move."</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
