<br />

<br />
Rice isn't <span style="font-weight: bold">that</span> expensive in India. Think you will find that the actual costs of a *snicker* GM there is considerably less than you budgeted figure.
<br />

<br />
One Indian working 50 hour weeks (it is India for crying out loud... work 50 or starve!) you will need 3.36 Indians for a full weeks coverage 24/7. Of course you will need multiple people during peak times and coverage over  multiple servers... ok..
<br />

<br />
Lets give ... ohhh  2 GMs per during peak times... lets say a 40 server coverage (they can roll amongst the servers based upon demand) ... scale back to 1 person coverage in the "US off hours" when numbers are decreasced.
<br />

<br />
/click click wirrrr click wirrrr....
<br />

<br />
Makes about 202 people to have full coverage time 40 servers... @ 10k a year... well. That’s a whopping $2.0 million or so.
<br />

<br />
WOW!!! $2.0 MILLION I hear everyone scream... hell of a lot of moolah!
<br />

<br />
BUT HARK.... $2.0 million is only 3% of the revenue stream. Trust me when I say this... this is nothing.... NOTHING....<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">NOTHING!!!</span>
<br />

<br />
HELL.. lets be nice to the Indians and pay then 20k a year instead... STILL only 6% of the revenue stream.
<br />

<br />
Perspective everyone...  SoE is cutting the fat and gobbling on that 3% that almost everyone is bitching is wrong with the game. Perspective really paints SoE as a money grubbing so and so without concern for service.
<br />

<br />
As for the cost of developing expansions...$29.95 time oh... lets say 200,000 as not everyone will buy it. Thats 6 million right there. These expansions self fund easy.
<br />

<br />
So what is left? OH yea... Smedleys salary.............
<br />

<br />
If your there Smed... SoE has been sucking this cash cow dry for too long! Give some grass back!
